  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Out-patient Appointment - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment">Out-Patient Appointment</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment">APPOINTMENT</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment">Out-Patient Appointment</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_appointment">APPOINTMENT</xref>
 for a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 to see or have contact with a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
 at an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_out-patient_clinic">Out-Patient Clinic</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
Each 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment">Out-Patient Appointment</xref>
 is either an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment_consultant">Out-Patient Appointment Consultant</xref>
 or an 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment_non-consultant">Out-Patient Appointment Non-Consultant</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
